WEBVTT

00:02.753 --> 00:04.630
[McKenna] <i>Previously</i>
<i>on</i> Light as a Feather...

00:04.630 --> 00:05.964
[Alex] Who are you bringing
to Olivia's party?

00:05.964 --> 00:06.965
[Henry] <i>You want to go together?</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:08.342
‐Yeah.
‐Okay.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.718
Don't tell me
this is another one

00:09.718 --> 00:11.386
of your Halloween prank
thingies.

00:11.386 --> 00:13.388
She's a little awkward,
but what's the problem

00:13.388 --> 00:15.182
with just having her
come for one night?

00:15.182 --> 00:16.808
‐Let's invite her.
‐Cool.

00:16.808 --> 00:19.770
I got you something.
It's the dress you wanted.

00:19.770 --> 00:21.021
We have to do
something spooky.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.272
How about Light as a Feather,

00:22.272 --> 00:23.273
Stiff as a Board?

00:23.273 --> 00:24.691
The leader tells a story

00:24.691 --> 00:25.859
about how the person
is going to die.

00:25.859 --> 00:27.778
Olivia flew down the highway.

00:27.778 --> 00:29.947
<i>‐By the time</i>
<i>she saw the truck...</i>
<i>‐[screams]</i>

00:29.947 --> 00:31.615
<i>it was too late.</i>

00:31.615 --> 00:33.825
[Olivia] Severed arm
on the freeway. Pretty twisted.

00:33.825 --> 00:35.494
So who wants to go next?

00:37.204 --> 00:40.541
[Violet] Alex Portnoy was never
at a loss for words

00:40.541 --> 00:42.751
until her last moments on earth.

00:42.751 --> 00:45.546
[gasping]

00:45.546 --> 00:47.756
She looked so small
lying there,

00:47.756 --> 00:50.467
<i>choking, terrified,</i>

00:50.467 --> 00:52.761
<i>wordlessly pleading.</i>

00:52.761 --> 00:54.554
<i>But no one could help.</i>

00:54.554 --> 00:57.474
<i>They say ten minutes</i>
<i>without oxygen</i>

00:57.474 --> 01:00.102
<i>will leave somebody</i>
<i>brain damaged for life.</i>

01:00.102 --> 01:02.104
<i>Maybe Alex got lucky.</i>

01:02.104 --> 01:04.398
<i>Her heart stopped after five.</i>

01:04.398 --> 01:06.650
‐[music playing]
‐[screaming]

01:06.650 --> 01:11.154
<i>♪ Everybody's talkin',</i>
<i>talkin' ♪</i>

01:11.154 --> 01:12.406
[Alex] Aah!

01:12.406 --> 01:14.866
Literally
the best Halloween ever!

01:14.866 --> 01:16.785
[McKenna] I cannot believe
that Isaac's sister

01:16.785 --> 01:18.287
got us into a college party.

01:18.287 --> 01:20.122
[Candace]
Technically junior college.

01:20.122 --> 01:21.623
What's your problem?

01:21.623 --> 01:23.000
[Alex] Is this still
about the graveyard?

01:23.000 --> 01:25.669
As a matter of fact,
yes, it is.

01:25.669 --> 01:27.671
What? Am I the only one
that thought

01:27.671 --> 01:29.715
that that game
was seriously messed up?

01:29.715 --> 01:30.924
I thought it was funny.

01:30.924 --> 01:32.467
[McKenna]
Violet is unique,

01:32.467 --> 01:34.011
but she's just trying
to make friends.

01:34.011 --> 01:35.679
[Olivia] Plus we did
such a nice thing.

01:35.679 --> 01:36.930
[Alex] Ohh!

01:36.930 --> 01:39.099
[Olivia]
Where is she anyway?

01:39.099 --> 01:42.477
You know, probably off
predicting the deaths
of random strangers.

01:42.477 --> 01:43.979
[laughter]

01:46.898 --> 01:48.108
Shoot, I need to find her.

01:48.108 --> 01:50.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:50.902 --> 01:52.529
What? She's my ride.

02:05.208 --> 02:07.210
Two hours past curfew?

02:07.210 --> 02:09.254
How bad is your mom
gonna kill you?

02:09.254 --> 02:12.049
I guess I'm gonna
have to find out.

02:13.300 --> 02:16.803
Hey, McKenna,
thanks again for tonight.

02:16.803 --> 02:19.431
I'm sorry if that game
creeped you guys out.

02:19.431 --> 02:20.891
Oh, trust me.

02:20.891 --> 02:23.769
I mean, maybe a little,
but it's fine.

02:23.769 --> 02:26.355
Okay, cool.

02:26.355 --> 02:28.690
Hey, if you want,
we can make something up.

02:28.690 --> 02:31.068
Tell your mom I had car trouble

02:31.068 --> 02:33.445
or your phone's dead.

02:33.445 --> 02:35.405
Oh, it's fine.

02:35.405 --> 02:38.241
I'll‐‐ I'll handle it.

02:38.241 --> 02:39.993
‐Good night.
‐Good night.

02:43.121 --> 02:45.666
I'll hold
onto the dress for you.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.125
Thanks.

03:02.557 --> 03:05.185
‐Aah!
‐Shit! You scared me!

03:05.185 --> 03:06.853
[Deb] 1:00 a. m.? Jeez!

03:06.853 --> 03:08.689
Whatever you were doing,
I hope it was worth it,

03:08.689 --> 03:10.565
because you are grounded.

03:10.565 --> 03:12.818
What? Mom, no.

03:12.818 --> 03:14.152
Olivia's party's on Saturday.

03:14.152 --> 03:16.363
You know I'm going
with Henry.

03:16.363 --> 03:18.990
You should have thought
of that before you
missed curfew, McKenna.

03:18.990 --> 03:20.158
What were you thinking?

03:20.158 --> 03:21.368
This isn't like you.

03:21.368 --> 03:22.953
[McKenna]
Yeah, exactly.

03:22.953 --> 03:25.497
I literally
never do anything wrong.

03:25.497 --> 03:27.374
Can you please
just let this slide

03:27.374 --> 03:28.792
like a normal parent? Please?!

03:28.792 --> 03:30.419
Well, I'm not
a normal parent, McKenna.

03:30.419 --> 03:32.045
Trust me, I wish I were.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.171
Okay, so what?

03:33.171 --> 03:34.798
What about me?

03:34.798 --> 03:38.218
When do I get to be
normal again?

03:38.218 --> 03:40.429
We'll talk about this
in the morning.

03:40.429 --> 03:41.888
I'm glad you're not dead.

03:44.808 --> 03:46.601
[sighs]

03:54.526 --> 03:57.112
[theme music playing]

04:02.534 --> 04:05.579
[bell rings]

04:10.250 --> 04:12.752
Hey, McKenna, what happened
with your mom yesterday?

04:12.752 --> 04:14.880
Oh, um, grounded.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.756
Oh, shit.

04:16.756 --> 04:18.425
What about Olivia's party?

04:18.425 --> 04:19.759
What about Henry?

04:19.759 --> 04:22.095
Um, haven't exactly
told Henry,

04:22.095 --> 04:25.348
but, um,
what am I supposed to do?

04:25.348 --> 04:27.601
Whatever it takes.

04:27.601 --> 04:29.144
Well, he goes back
to USC next Sunday.

04:29.144 --> 04:31.313
This was
kind of my only shot.

04:31.313 --> 04:34.357
Well, then blow off your mom
and go to the party.

04:34.357 --> 04:37.444
I can't do that.
There's no way.

04:37.444 --> 04:39.529
McKenna, there's always a way.

04:41.448 --> 04:44.576
As I promised when I was running
for class president,

04:44.576 --> 04:47.496
this year, 30% of proceeds
from fundraisers

04:47.496 --> 04:50.499
will go towards
the Willow Falls High
anti‐bullying initiative.

04:50.499 --> 04:53.293
[Noreen] Bullying?
You mean like the other day

04:53.293 --> 04:55.504
when your little machine
sprayed red crap
all over the new girl?

04:55.504 --> 04:57.255
[Olivia]
That wasn't bullying, Noreen.

04:57.255 --> 04:59.591
That was an unfortunate mishap.

04:59.591 --> 05:01.051
Right, Violet?

05:02.636 --> 05:04.221
Oh, definitely.

05:04.221 --> 05:07.349
Violet's even coming
to my party Saturday.

05:07.349 --> 05:08.975
Would a bully do that?

05:08.975 --> 05:11.144
So, anyway, 30% of proceeds.

05:11.144 --> 05:14.189
We need to figure out
what fundraisers we're doing.

05:19.569 --> 05:21.988
["Sweat" by Hayz playing
in gymnasium]

05:21.988 --> 05:25.116
<i>♪ Ooh ooh‐ooh‐ooh ooh ♪</i>

05:25.116 --> 05:27.536
<i>♪ Ooh ooh‐ooh‐ooh ooh ♪</i>

05:27.536 --> 05:29.621
<i>♪ Make you sweat ♪</i>

05:29.621 --> 05:31.164
<i>♪ Like a fever ♪</i>

05:31.164 --> 05:32.833
<i>♪ On your knees ♪</i>

05:32.833 --> 05:34.209
<i>♪ A believer ♪</i>

05:34.209 --> 05:38.129
<i>♪ So sweat, sweat ♪</i>

05:38.129 --> 05:42.384
<i>♪ I hope you got</i>
<i>your hallelujahs saved up now ♪</i>

05:45.220 --> 05:46.263
Looking kind of sluggish
there, Portnoy.

05:46.263 --> 05:47.430
Everything okay?

05:47.430 --> 05:49.266
Hundred percent, coach.

05:49.266 --> 05:50.892
Hey, whoa, whoa.
Hold on.

05:50.892 --> 05:54.354
You'd tell me if something
was going on, right?

05:54.354 --> 05:57.190
Honestly, probably not.

05:57.190 --> 05:58.400
Don't worry.

05:58.400 --> 05:59.734
I'm fine.

06:05.991 --> 06:07.951
[knock on door]

06:09.411 --> 06:12.664
‐[dog whines]
‐Moxie.

06:12.664 --> 06:14.875
Keeps sneaking into our yard
through the hole in your fence,

06:14.875 --> 06:16.167
so I fixed it.

06:16.167 --> 06:17.669
Poor baby.

06:17.669 --> 06:20.338
She probably misses
hangin' out with me.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.843
Listen, about what I said
to you the other day.

06:24.843 --> 06:26.303
Um, you know,
I'm kind of busy,

06:26.303 --> 06:28.555
uh, getting ready
for something, so...

06:28.555 --> 06:31.766
Oh, right. Olivia Richmond's
masturbatory crap‐fest.

06:31.766 --> 06:34.936
Mm, you sound really jealous
you weren't invited.

06:34.936 --> 06:36.605
You kidding?

06:36.605 --> 06:38.481
I got tickets to Mike Watt
in Modesto tonight.

06:38.481 --> 06:39.816
Great.

06:39.816 --> 06:41.276
Have fun with that.

06:43.778 --> 06:46.406
[Trey] You're welcome
for rescuing your dog.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.245
And fixing your fence.

06:55.081 --> 06:57.042
[Gloria]
<i>I got a surprise for you.</i>

06:58.126 --> 07:00.003
I know it's not brand‐new.

07:00.003 --> 07:01.546
No, no. Thanks, Mom.

07:01.546 --> 07:03.506
It'll go great with my dress.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.760
So it's Olivia's big night, huh?

07:06.760 --> 07:08.803
18 years old.

07:08.803 --> 07:11.014
Yeah, it should be huge.

07:11.014 --> 07:14.476
You know, Olivia
is like my own daughter,

07:14.476 --> 07:17.646
but tonight, when everybody's
fussing about her,

07:17.646 --> 07:19.314
I want you to remember
one thing.

07:19.314 --> 07:21.232
Yeah?

07:23.276 --> 07:27.447
You are never in that
girl's shadow, Candace Preston.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.742
Don't you ever forget that.

07:32.160 --> 07:34.371
Thanks, Mom.

08:17.997 --> 08:20.250
[McKenna]
Gotta go.

08:20.250 --> 08:21.793
Library and then home.

08:21.793 --> 08:23.712
Listen, if you decide
to knock off early,

08:23.712 --> 08:25.130
maybe we could
do something later.

08:25.130 --> 08:27.716
We could, um, watch TV,
order pizza.

08:27.716 --> 08:29.092
Maybe.

08:38.518 --> 08:39.728
[car horn honks]

08:39.728 --> 08:42.397
[muffled dance music playing]

08:49.529 --> 08:53.283
[McKenna screams and laughs]

08:54.659 --> 08:55.994
Hi!

08:55.994 --> 08:57.912
Here we go, right?

09:00.081 --> 09:02.667
<i>♪ Yeah, get down, get down ♪</i>

09:02.667 --> 09:05.462
<i>♪ Get down, get down ♪</i>

09:05.462 --> 09:06.963
[Candace] <i>Voilà.</i>

09:06.963 --> 09:09.841
You, Ms. Brady, look
one hell of a lot better.

09:09.841 --> 09:11.634
Dress, please.

09:11.634 --> 09:13.595
Thank you.

09:17.474 --> 09:19.642
Whoa, whoa, what's this?

09:19.642 --> 09:21.686
Um, it's my dress.

09:21.686 --> 09:23.938
‐You bought it?
‐With what?
Did you sell a kidney?

09:23.938 --> 09:25.648
[Alex]
More like three kidneys.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.233
Uh, no, Violet got it for me.

09:27.233 --> 09:29.319
‐[Candace] What?
‐[Violet] It's no big deal.

09:29.319 --> 09:31.529
Look, that dress costs,
like, 400 bucks.
You barely know her.

09:31.529 --> 09:33.823
‐I was just trying
to be nice.
‐And you were.

09:33.823 --> 09:35.658
No, no.
See, no one's that nice.

09:35.658 --> 09:37.285
That right there
is just some psycho shit.

09:37.285 --> 09:38.495
I'm sorry you feel that way.

09:38.495 --> 09:39.996
[McKenna]
Candace, chill.

09:39.996 --> 09:41.331
Violet's the only reason
I can even come tonight.

09:41.331 --> 09:43.416
She had the idea
to hide my phone.

09:43.416 --> 09:45.418
[choking]

09:45.418 --> 09:46.628
Oh, my God.

09:46.628 --> 09:48.296
She's choking.

09:54.094 --> 09:56.471
‐Does anyone know CPR?
‐No, not you.

09:56.471 --> 09:58.348
‐[choking]
‐Come on, Alex.

09:58.348 --> 10:00.517
Come on.

10:00.517 --> 10:02.560
[grunting]

10:02.560 --> 10:05.438
‐[laughing]
‐You little bitch.

10:05.438 --> 10:06.898
You were just faking?

10:06.898 --> 10:08.900
If it'd been real,
I'd be dead now.

10:08.900 --> 10:11.736
‐It's not funny, Alex.
‐It's a joke!

10:13.238 --> 10:14.697
Fooled me.

10:14.697 --> 10:17.742
[rock music playing]

10:17.742 --> 10:21.830
<i>♪ Yeah, I know</i>
<i>that you're no good, good ♪</i>

10:21.830 --> 10:25.166
<i>♪ In fact I know you're</i>
<i>straight up wrong for me ♪</i>

10:25.166 --> 10:26.626
[McKenna] Wow.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.503
Red carpet, seriously?

10:28.503 --> 10:30.463
Well, Candace, you always
wanted to step and repeat.

10:30.463 --> 10:32.757
I'm still not talking to you.

10:32.757 --> 10:33.967
[Olivia] Hey, guys.

10:33.967 --> 10:35.009
Hey!

10:35.009 --> 10:36.761
Did you see my new ride?

10:36.761 --> 10:39.013
‐Yeah. It's amazing.
‐Wow!

10:39.013 --> 10:41.808
Um, I'm gonna
get us some drinks.

10:46.396 --> 10:47.939
Hey, you.

10:48.815 --> 10:50.024
Hi.

10:50.024 --> 10:52.610
‐Shall we?
‐We shall.

11:16.176 --> 11:18.344
[water running]

11:18.344 --> 11:22.307
["Pink Cadillac" by Alice Gray
playing in party]

11:22.307 --> 11:27.103
<i>♪ Yellow love, meet</i>
<i>the sunglasses on my eyes ♪</i>

11:27.103 --> 11:28.980
<i>♪ On my eyes ♪</i>

11:28.980 --> 11:33.067
<i>♪ Never let anyone see</i>
<i>the things I hide ♪</i>

11:33.067 --> 11:36.237
<i>♪ Show me what it feels like ♪</i>

11:36.237 --> 11:37.822
<i>♪ They don't know me ♪</i>

11:37.822 --> 11:39.449
I'm gonna go check
with the bartender.

11:39.449 --> 11:41.075
I don't want to run
out of ice.

11:41.075 --> 11:42.493
The ice is fine.

11:42.493 --> 11:44.454
Come on, Livs,
focus on us for a second.

11:44.454 --> 11:46.998
I mean, you barely
even mentioned your gift.

11:48.208 --> 11:49.834
I'm sorry.

11:49.834 --> 11:51.544
You're right. I haven't.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.379
I'm just still
in party‐planning mode.

11:53.379 --> 11:55.423
<i>♪ I just wanna feel right ♪</i>

11:55.423 --> 11:57.759
It's gorgeous.

11:57.759 --> 11:59.469
Thank you.

11:59.469 --> 12:03.056
<i>♪ I don't wanna be let down ♪</i>

12:03.056 --> 12:06.559
<i>I don't wanna let you go ♪</i>

12:06.559 --> 12:09.562
<i>♪ Baby, we can take it fast ♪</i>

12:09.562 --> 12:12.065
<i>♪ And maybe we can</i>
<i>drive real slow ♪</i>

12:12.065 --> 12:13.608
I'm really glad you came.

12:13.608 --> 12:15.818
Me, too.

12:15.818 --> 12:17.403
Even though
it practically seems like

12:17.403 --> 12:19.405
you had to fake
your own death to get here.

12:19.405 --> 12:21.115
Oh. [laughs]

12:21.115 --> 12:22.992
I mean, it wasn't
that much trouble.

12:22.992 --> 12:25.495
‐Close. Near death.
‐Near death.

12:25.495 --> 12:27.288
[D.J., on P. A. system]
<i>Okay, now we have some people</i>

12:27.288 --> 12:29.082
<i>who'd like</i>
<i>to say a few words.</i>

12:29.082 --> 12:30.833
Oh. There are speeches?

12:30.833 --> 12:33.002
Want to get out of here
for a while?

12:33.002 --> 12:34.587
Yeah.

12:42.553 --> 12:45.265
[feedback squeals]

12:45.265 --> 12:47.183
When we think
of Olivia Richmond,

12:47.183 --> 12:49.519
we think about
all her accomplishments‐‐

12:49.519 --> 12:52.438
sports, student government,
community service.

12:52.438 --> 12:56.192
But, having grown up
as one of her very best friends,

12:56.192 --> 12:59.279
I happen to know some things
about her that you don't.

12:59.279 --> 13:03.908
For example, did you know
that our friend Olivia

13:03.908 --> 13:08.579
is an absolutely terrible

13:08.579 --> 13:10.248
shoplifter?

13:10.248 --> 13:13.876
[laughing]

13:15.128 --> 13:17.297
It happened once
three years ago.

13:17.297 --> 13:19.090
Cheap phone case.

13:19.090 --> 13:21.926
The security guy at Target
let her off with a warning.

13:21.926 --> 13:24.554
Not gonna speculate
how that happened.

13:24.554 --> 13:26.347
[feedback squeals]

13:26.347 --> 13:27.932
[clears throat]

13:27.932 --> 13:29.350
Man, it's, um...

13:29.350 --> 13:31.352
It's hot‐‐ it's hot up here.

13:32.687 --> 13:34.230
‐Cheers.
‐Cheers.

13:35.690 --> 13:38.735
Thanks for hangin' out
with me.

13:38.735 --> 13:40.236
I really wasn't looking forward

13:40.236 --> 13:41.738
to hanging out
with those people tonight.

13:41.738 --> 13:44.282
Really? Thought it would be
fun for you,

13:44.282 --> 13:48.411
talking about USC
and all your accomplishments.

13:48.411 --> 13:50.580
Oh, you mean the ones my parents
are in there bragging about.

13:50.580 --> 13:55.418
Well, you know,
you're Henry Richmond.

13:55.418 --> 13:56.794
You're kind of a big deal.

13:56.794 --> 13:59.130
Maybe here,

13:59.130 --> 14:01.799
but at USC...

14:05.219 --> 14:07.305
If I tell you something,

14:07.305 --> 14:09.307
you mind keeping it
to yourself?

14:10.475 --> 14:11.726
Sure.

14:13.436 --> 14:14.854
I quit the tennis team.

14:14.854 --> 14:17.356
Oh. Be‐‐
because of your knee?

14:17.356 --> 14:19.567
Because I'm not that good.

14:19.567 --> 14:21.944
I was great here.

14:21.944 --> 14:24.572
Once you get to school
with 19,000 other people,

14:24.572 --> 14:26.324
you start to realize

14:26.324 --> 14:28.034
there are a whole lot
of Henry Richmonds

14:28.034 --> 14:29.619
from a whole lot
of Willow Falls.

14:29.619 --> 14:32.789
Well, what did your parents say?

14:34.082 --> 14:36.626
You're kind of the first person
I've told.

14:38.377 --> 14:40.129
Why me?

14:41.923 --> 14:43.466
I don't know.

14:43.466 --> 14:46.427
I guess at some point
I got it in my head

14:46.427 --> 14:48.971
that you're someone
I want to tell things to.

14:49.847 --> 14:51.557
Since when?

14:51.557 --> 14:54.018
Since the other day
when I saw you in that dress.

14:57.355 --> 14:59.440
[Deb] Nice dress.

14:59.440 --> 15:00.733
Must be new.

15:00.733 --> 15:02.777
Say your goodbyes.
We're going.

15:07.532 --> 15:09.200
Mom, you are humiliating me.

15:09.200 --> 15:13.830
‐Maybe you deserve it.
‐I'm sorry.

15:13.830 --> 15:15.206
Hey, birthday girl.

15:15.206 --> 15:16.707
I thought now might be
a good time

15:16.707 --> 15:18.292
for those group shots
with your friends?

15:19.252 --> 15:20.753
What friends?

15:23.923 --> 15:27.426
We do not lie in this family,
McKenna Brady.

15:27.426 --> 15:29.178
‐Where's your phone?
‐I don't know. You tell me.

15:29.178 --> 15:31.139
You're the one who's been
tracking me all night.

15:31.139 --> 15:33.141
What, did someone tag me
in a photo or something?

15:33.141 --> 15:34.934
It's a good thing
they did, too.

15:34.934 --> 15:37.019
Breaking curfew,
sneaking out to parties?

15:37.019 --> 15:39.814
God knows where that dress
came from.

15:41.274 --> 15:43.860
I'm sorry.
Are you‐‐ are you drunk?

15:45.736 --> 15:46.863
Get in the car.

15:46.863 --> 15:50.283
Give me your keys, now!

15:50.283 --> 15:51.534
[keys jingle]

15:52.785 --> 15:54.120
[Olivia]
<i>My party has become</i>

15:54.120 --> 15:56.247
a complete
and total shit show.

15:56.247 --> 15:57.999
Isaac's acting weird,

15:57.999 --> 15:59.917
and Alex just outed me
as a felon

15:59.917 --> 16:01.460
in front of my grandparents.

16:01.460 --> 16:03.129
And McKenna's mom
just showed up

16:03.129 --> 16:05.131
lit as a goddamn Christmas tree.

16:05.131 --> 16:07.508
And‐‐ Oh, by the way,

16:07.508 --> 16:10.553
where the hell are you,
Candace Preston?

16:10.553 --> 16:12.471
Call me back now!

16:12.471 --> 16:14.015
[knock on door]

16:16.350 --> 16:17.768
What?

16:17.768 --> 16:19.228
Nothing.

16:19.228 --> 16:20.813
I'm sorry.

16:20.813 --> 16:22.940
Maybe this will help?

16:22.940 --> 16:24.567
What is it?

16:24.567 --> 16:26.068
Rum.

16:33.659 --> 16:34.911
Thanks.

16:34.911 --> 16:36.412
No problem.

16:36.412 --> 16:38.873
And if it helps,
I think I know where Candace is.

16:42.877 --> 16:45.213
Whoa, whoa, hold on a minute.

16:45.213 --> 16:47.548
We have to stop.
We've been gone way too long.

16:48.966 --> 16:50.718
[whispering]
Maybe I don't care anymore.

16:50.718 --> 16:53.262
Well, I do, Isaac.

16:53.262 --> 16:55.765
I don't know, and, just...

16:55.765 --> 17:00.478
until I can speak to Olivia,
we have to stop.

17:00.478 --> 17:01.854
Okay?

17:16.953 --> 17:18.704
Olivia, wait.

17:23.668 --> 17:25.294
Olivia, wait.

17:25.294 --> 17:26.671
Where are you going?

17:26.671 --> 17:28.047
Anywhere but here.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.591
Look, you're upset.
I understand,

17:30.591 --> 17:33.219
but you've been drinking.
At least let me drive.

17:33.219 --> 17:35.930
Please, you have so many people
that care about you.

17:35.930 --> 17:37.306
I care!

17:39.016 --> 17:40.977
[tires squeal]

17:44.981 --> 17:46.649
[screams]

17:50.736 --> 17:53.739
[punching touchscreen]

17:53.739 --> 17:55.825
<i>[line ringing]</i>

17:57.159 --> 17:58.703
<i>[ringing]</i>

18:01.205 --> 18:02.832
<i>[ringing]</i>

18:02.832 --> 18:04.458
<i>You've reached Candace.</i>

18:04.458 --> 18:05.626
<i>Either I'm not here</i>
<i>to take your call</i>

18:05.626 --> 18:07.086
<i>or I'm completely ignoring you.</i>

18:07.086 --> 18:08.296
[beep]

18:08.296 --> 18:10.423
You backstabber.

18:10.423 --> 18:13.009
You ruined my night,
now you won't take my calls?

18:13.009 --> 18:16.554
Yeah, well, I hope making out
with my boyfriend was worth it.

18:16.554 --> 18:19.432
Because, bitch,
you are dead to me!

18:19.432 --> 18:20.933
You and I are completely‐‐

18:20.933 --> 18:22.476
‐[screams]
‐[horn honks]

18:25.688 --> 18:27.815
[crying and whimpering]

18:27.815 --> 18:30.610
[warning bell dinging]

18:48.711 --> 18:52.006
Wow. Looks like somebody's
having a shitty birthday.

19:00.681 --> 19:02.683
How about a ride?

19:09.440 --> 19:12.318
[fluttering sound]

19:36.759 --> 19:40.137
[chewing fingernails]

19:54.276 --> 19:55.945
<i>Hey, it's Livvy.</i>

19:55.945 --> 19:57.571
<i>Please leave</i>
<i>your birthday message here.</i>

19:57.571 --> 19:58.698
[beep]

19:58.698 --> 20:01.409
["Runaways" by Lowell playing]

20:04.995 --> 20:08.374
<i>♪ You say I'm bad to the bone ♪</i>

20:08.374 --> 20:11.836
<i>♪ 'Cause my blood runs cold ♪</i>

20:11.836 --> 20:13.629
<i>♪ And the dealer, he folds ♪</i>

20:13.629 --> 20:14.964
‐[knock on door]
<i>‐♪ But he can't ♪</i>

20:14.964 --> 20:16.340
<i>♪ And he won't walk away ♪</i>

20:16.340 --> 20:18.551
<i>♪ Ohh oh ♪</i>

20:26.851 --> 20:28.686
‐Hey.
‐Hey.

20:28.686 --> 20:30.438
You scared me.
What are you doing here?

20:30.438 --> 20:33.733
Sorry.
I thought you might need this.

20:33.733 --> 20:35.693
Thank you.
Wait, how did you‐‐

20:35.693 --> 20:37.987
Your friend told me
where to find it.

20:37.987 --> 20:39.613
Wait. Which friend?

20:39.613 --> 20:41.615
Uh, that‐‐ that new girl.

20:41.615 --> 20:43.909
I don't remember her name.

20:49.290 --> 20:51.000
Do you want to come in?

20:51.000 --> 20:52.793
Okay.

20:52.793 --> 20:55.838
<i>♪ You and me till the end ♪</i>

20:55.838 --> 20:58.090
<i>♪ Gonna run away</i>
<i>until they understand ♪</i>

20:58.090 --> 21:00.217
<i>♪ Ohh, to the sun ♪</i>

21:00.217 --> 21:02.511
<i>‐♪ Where the river runs dry ♪</i>
<i>‐[line ringing]</i>

21:02.511 --> 21:05.306
‐[cell phone rings]
<i>‐♪ I was gone</i>
<i>in the blink of an eye ♪</i>

21:05.306 --> 21:07.725
‐Hey.
‐Hey, um...

21:07.725 --> 21:10.352
you haven't by chance
heard from Olivia?

21:10.352 --> 21:12.855
No. No, why? Why?
What'd she say?

21:12.855 --> 21:15.691
Nothing. It's just, uh, she
hasn't been answering her phone,

21:15.691 --> 21:17.902
and I've been seeing
all these things about‐‐

21:17.902 --> 21:20.821
<i>Police confirm a teenage girl</i>
<i>was killed in the crash.</i>

21:20.821 --> 21:23.324
<i>The victim's name</i>
<i>has not been released</i>

21:23.324 --> 21:25.868
<i>pending a family notification.</i>

21:27.620 --> 21:30.623
[gasping]

21:30.623 --> 21:32.541
Hello?

21:32.541 --> 21:33.876
Allie?

21:40.174 --> 21:43.344
<i>‐♪ Into the deep of the blue ♪</i>
<i>‐[phone vibrating]</i>

21:43.344 --> 21:45.513
<i>‐♪ Ride and die with you ♪</i>
<i>‐Sorry.</i>

21:45.513 --> 21:47.223
Keeps ringing.

21:47.223 --> 21:49.600
<i>‐♪ On the out looking in ♪</i>
<i>‐It's Alex.</i>

21:49.600 --> 21:51.685
<i>♪ But the walls,</i>
<i>they're all paper thin ♪</i>

21:51.685 --> 21:53.395
Hey.

21:53.395 --> 21:56.190
<i>♪ I'm not sorry</i>
<i>for the insanity ♪</i>

21:56.190 --> 21:58.651
<i>♪ We're racing to the end</i>
<i>to meet ♪</i>

21:58.651 --> 22:00.945
Hey, McKenna.

22:00.945 --> 22:03.113
Is everything okay?

22:04.532 --> 22:06.575
What's wrong? What's happened?

22:08.744 --> 22:11.247
Miraculously, the driver
of the car escaped

22:11.247 --> 22:13.791
with only minor injuries.

22:13.791 --> 22:18.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:31.308 --> 22:35.688
[music playing]
